&lt;h1 id="nullius-in-verba"&gt;Nullius in Verba&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mar 5 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nullius in Verba&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Take no one&amp;rsquo;s word for it&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Naval:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Beginning of Infinity&lt;/em&gt; is not an easy book to read. Deutsch wrote it for other physicists and philosophers. He has a certain peer group that he respects, and that respects him, and he has to meet them at their level.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Ask yourself dumb questions – and answer them!</title><link>https://linguista.cn/person/terencetao/career-advice/orig/ask-yourself-dumb-questions-and-answer-them/</link><pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 18:57:12 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/person/terencetao/career-advice/orig/ask-yourself-dumb-questions-and-answer-them/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/person/terencetao/career-advice/zh/ask-yourself-dumb-questions-and-answer-them.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;
